---
import Layout from "../layouts/BlogPost.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Me : Naresh Jois"
  description="About Naresh Jois and what I do"
  pubDate={new Date("February 18 2026")}
>
  <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">
    The Architect Behind the Data (and the Stove)
  </h2>
  <p class="mb-8">
    I'm technically supposed to write a professional "About Me" section here,
    but let's be real: you're probably just checking to see if I'm a bot or a
    real human with a movie obsession. Spoiler: It's the latter.
  </p>
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">The Day Job</h3>
  <p class="mb-8">
    By day, I'm a Product Architect at Infoveave, where I spend my time
    obsessing over building a unified data platform. If it involves making data
    work harder so humans can work smarter, I'm probably building it. I've spent
    the last 16+ years architecting solutions for everyone from massive
    enterprises to scrappy medium-sized businesses. Before Infoveave, I was the
    guy behind the scenes building large scale systems liked igital reward platforms,
    used by some of India's biggest banks.
  </p>
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">The "After-Hours" Résumé</h3>
  <p class="mb-8">
    When I'm not wrangling data, I'm likely busy being a "Professional Amateur"
    at several hobbies:
    <ul>
      <li class="mb-4">
        Cinephile Extraordinaire: I have watched at least 3,000 movies. That's
        roughly 6,000 hours (or 250 straight days) of cinematic intake. I am
        essentially a walking IMDb database at this point.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-4">
        Kitchen Chemist: I'm an amateur chef. I haven't won a Michelin star yet,
        but I haven't burned the kitchen down either. Progress!
      </li>
      <li class="mb-4">
        The Creative Hustle: In my remaining five minutes of free time, I dabble
        in photography and video editing, mostly to prove that my life has a
        cinematic aesthetic
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">Let's Chat</h3>
  <p class="mb-8">
     Whether you want to talk about data architecture, the best way to
    make a dosa, or why that one 1990s cult classic is underrated, hit me up.
    Find me here: @nareshjois (I promise I'll get back to you faster than a SQL
    query on a good day.)
  </p>
</Layout>
